pathData = "~/R/HW9/hw_09/Data/stock_dfs"
path = "~/R/HW9/hw_09/Data"
names = list.files(pathData, pattern = "*.csv")
stat = read_csv(paste(path, "constituents.csv", sep = '/'))
yearlyGainRep = data.frame()
thirteenDay = data.frame()
for(i in names){
    crt = read_csv(paste(pathData, i, sep = '/'))
    crt %>% mutate(name = substr(i, 1, nchar(i)-4), year = substr(Date, 1, 4)) -> crt
    crt %>% group_by(year) %>% summarise(gain = (tail(Close, 1) - Open[1]) / Open[1] * 100, Symbol = name[1]) -> rep
    yearlyGainRep = bind_rows(yearlyGainRep, rep)
    crt %>% filter(substr(Date, 9, 10) == "13") -> thirteens
    thirteenDay =  bind_rows(thirteenDay, thirteens)
}

twoYearGainRep = data.frame()
for (i in symbolList) {
    crt = yearlyGainRep %>% filter(Symbol == i)
    if(length(crt$year) >= 3){
        crt %>% mutate(gain = movavg(gain, 2, "s")*2) %>% slice(2:n()) -> crt
        year = as.numeric(crt$year)
        prevYear = as.character(year-1)
        crt$year = paste(prevYear, year, sep = "-")
        crt$year = substr(crt$year, 1, 9)
        twoYearGainRep = bind_rows(twoYearGainRep, crt)
    }
}
twoYearRep = twoYearGainRep %>% group_by(Sector) %>% arrange(desc(gain)) %>% slice(1:1)
print(twoYearRep)

. . .

We will use t test to see wether mean of gain is smaller than zero or not. 

thirteenDay = thirteenDay %>% mutate(gain = (Close - Open) / Open *100)
t.test(thirteenDay$gain, mu = 0, alternative = 'greater')
## 
##  One Sample t-test
## 
## data:  thirteenDay$gain
## t = 11.568, df = 65541, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true mean is greater than 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  0.08391949        Inf
## sample estimates:
##  mean of x 
## 0.09783038

As we can see in the test result, 13th is actually a good day to trade.

entire = data.frame()
for(i in names){
    crt = read_csv(paste(pathData, i, sep = '/'))
    crt %>% mutate(name = substr(i, 1, nchar(i)-4), year = substr(Date, 1, 4)) -> crt
    entire = crt %>% mutate(cap = Volume * abs(Close - Open)/2) %>% bind_rows(entire)
}
capRep = entire %>% group_by(Date) %>% summarise(cap = sum(cap)) %>% arrange(desc(cap)) %>% head(5)

appleData = entire %>% filter(name == "AAPL") %>% select(Date, Open)
k = 5
columns = colnames(appleData)
for (i in 1:k){
    eval(parse(text = paste0('appleData$colum', i, ' <- 0')))
    appleData[,i+2] = shift(appleData$Open, i)
    columns[[i+2]] = paste("Daysago", i, sep = "_")
}
colnames(appleData) = columns
appleData = appleData %>% slice(k+1:n())
fit = lm(data = appleData, formula = Open ~ Daysago_1 + Daysago_2 + Daysago_3)

. pca . . 

comps = entire %>% select(name) %>% distinct %>% unlist()
openPrices=  entire %>% filter(name == comps[1]) %>% select(Date, Open) -> openPrices
colnames(openPrices) = c("Date", comps[1])
for(i in 2:length(comps)){
    entire %>% filter(name == comps[[i]]) %>% select(Date, Open) -> crt
    colnames(crt) = c("Date", comps[[i]])
    openPrices = full_join(openPrices, crt)
}
openPrices = openPrices %>% na.omit()
openPrices %>% select(-Date) -> openPrices
pca = prcomp(openPrices, center = T, scale. = T)
eigv = round(pca$sdev^2/sum(pca$sdev^2)*100, 2)
eigv = data.frame(c(1:126),eigv)
names(eigv) = c('PCs','Variance')
eigv %>% mutate(cumPer = cumsum(Variance)/sum(Variance) * 100) -> eigv
plot(eigv %>% select(PCs, cumPer),type = "b",col = "darkblue",lwd = 2)

Three first principal components sum up to almost 80% of total variance.

sectors = stat %>% select(Sector) %>% distinct() %>% unlist()
entireWhole = entire %>% select(Open, Date, Symbol = name) %>% full_join(stat) %>% na.omit()
entireWhole %>% group_by(Sector, Date) %>% summarise(avgPrice = mean(Open)) -> res
openPrices =  res %>% filter(Sector == sectors[1])
openPrices %>% ungroup() %>% select(-Sector) -> openPrices
colnames(openPrices) = c("Date", sectors[1])
for(i in 2:length(sectors)){
    crt =  res %>% filter(Sector == sectors[i])
    crt %>% ungroup() %>% select(-Sector) -> crt
    colnames(crt) = c("Date", sectors[i])
    openPrices = crt %>% full_join(openPrices)
}
openPrices = openPrices %>% na.omit()
indexes = read_csv(paste(path, "indexes.csv", sep = "/"))
openPrices %>% full_join(indexes) %>% na.omit() -> openPricesandIndexes
pca = prcomp(openPricesandIndexes %>% select(-Date), scale. = T, center = T)
biplot(pca, cex = 0.7)

appleData = entire %>% filter(name == "AAPL") %>% select(Date, Open, High, Close, Low, Volume)
pca = prcomp(appleData %>% select(-Date), center = T, scale. = T)
appleData$comp1 = t(t(pca$rotation[,1]) %*% t(appleData %>% select(-Date)))
appleData = appleData %>% select(Date, Open, comp1)
k = 5
columns = colnames(appleData)
for (i in 1:k){
    eval(parse(text = paste0('appleData$colum', i, ' <- 0')))
    appleData[,i+3] = shift(appleData$comp1, i)
    columns[[i+3]] = paste("Daysago", i, sep = "_")
}
colnames(appleData) = columns
appleData = appleData %>% slice(k+1:n())
fit = lm(data = appleData, formula = Open ~ Daysago_1 + Daysago_2 + Daysago_3)

comps = entire %>% select(name) %>% distinct %>% unlist()
openPrices=  entire %>% filter(name == comps[1]) %>% select(Date, Open) -> openPrices
colnames(openPrices) = c("Date", comps[1])
for(i in 2:length(comps)){
    entire %>% filter(name == comps[[i]]) %>% select(Date, Open) -> crt
    colnames(crt) = c("Date", comps[[i]])
    openPrices = full_join(openPrices, crt)
}
openPrices = openPrices %>% na.omit()
pca = prcomp(openPrices %>% select(-Date), center = T, scale. = T)
featureVec = pca$rotation[,c(1:10)]
res = data.frame(t(t(featureVec) %*% t(openPrices %>% select(-Date))))
res$Date = openPrices$Date
res = full_join(res, SP %>% select(Date, gain)) %>% na.omit()
res$trainVal = shift(res$gain, 1, type = 'lead')
res = res %>% slice(1:(n()-1))
res$trainVal = ifelse(res$trainVal>=0, 1, 0)
fit = glm(data = res, formula = trainVal~PC1+PC2+PC3+PC4+PC5+PC6+PC7+PC8+PC9+PC10, family = 'binomial')
res$pred = predict.glm(fit, res, type = 'response')
res$pred = ifelse(res$pred>= 0.5, 1, 0)
prec = sum(res$pred == res$trainVal)/nrow(res) * 100
print(prec)
## [1] 100

. . pca . . 

library("EBImage")
pic = flip(readImage(paste(path, "stock.jpg", sep = "/")))
red.weigth   = .2989; green.weigth = .587; blue.weigth  = 0.114
img = red.weigth * imageData(pic)[,,1] +
    green.weigth * imageData(pic)[,,2] + blue.weigth  * imageData(pic)[,,3]
image(img, col = grey(seq(0, 1, length = 256)))
pca.img = prcomp(img, scale=TRUE)
chosen.components = 1:109
feature.vector = pca.img$rotation[,chosen.components]
compact.data = t(feature.vector) %*% t(img)
approx.img = t(feature.vector %*% compact.data) 
# image(approx.img, col = grey(seq(0, 1, length = 256)))
